    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in Panama (
                        Hines
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d168</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">168</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-02-09T09:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-02-09T09:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-09T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="168" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/2–946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hines</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-09T09:00:00-05:00">February 9, 1946—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Department’s circular telegram January 26, 7 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">8
                        a.m.</hi>]. In conversation with Foreign Minister<note n="49" xml:id="d168fn49">Ricardo J. Alfaro.</note> yesterday in briefly discussing
                    Argentine matters, I obtained the information which causes me to definitely feel
                    that no approach has been made to Panama on subject of dedication [<hi rend="italic">mediation?</hi>]. I am sure Foreign Minister shares view that
                    Argentina holds definite obligation not to one Republic but to all.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hines</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
